Job Description:
Introduction:
Regularly monitor, prepare the forecasting daily on regulation requirement, all ALCO reports to ensure that all of these on time. Develop assets and liabilities management and analyze the balance sheet to ensure the company has risk mitigation tools for effective and efficient cash management and uses the company's assets to maximize profitability and minimize financial risk.

Responsibilities:
•	Monitoring weekly and monthly ALCO Report;
•	Monitor and review forecasting report, cash flow and liquidity position, currency mismatching gape, Capital Adequacy level, and interest rate risk sensitivity analysis and NBC reports;
•	Develop/revise assets and liabilities management policy to maximize net interest income and minimize risks due to mismatch between assets and liabilities;
•	Liquidity Risk/ Currency Risk and Interest Rate Risk;
•	Be part of a team with specialized skills and knowledge;
•	Share and support on the role in charge and ensure alignment between ALM and Business Objective;
•	Ensure all the projects/ tasks assigned by management are delivered.

Job Requirement:
•	Degree in banking and finance, accounting or related fields;
•	Minimum 02 years’ experience in assets and liabilities management, or financial report background (report to NBC or to lenders);  
•	Good in communication skill;
•	Computer Literacy;
•	Ability to develop statements as per regulatory standards;
•	Good attitude, be honest, serious, gentle, friendly and willing to work.


