Job Description:
Develop practical collateral methodology as well as enhance existing ones aligning the current market environment to ensure risk mitigation adequate competitive advantages, customer and staff satisfaction.

Responsibilities: 
•	Analyze and conduct market survey & intelligence to be aware gaps between existing collateral methodology and implement and situation change;
•	Improve existing or new development on collateral methodology plat form to ensure loan security are well designed to mitigate risk, meet client or area situation and implementation;
•	Develop and enhancement collateral valuation guideline and disseminate the all collateral methodology guide to staff to ensure they understand the concepts and condition to implemented properly;
•	Supporting and reporting on collateral and/or property information follow to other requested from NBC, Lender and management;
•	Cooperate with related departments in identifying and developing systems and training methodology guide to ensure smooth and timely product launch activities with collateral risk mitigation;
•	Plan user acceptance testing (UAT), develop test scenarios and test cases for core banking system (CBS) and App;
•	Follow up and support staff to ensure proper implementation of policies and application of methodology guidelines and collection of feedback for better to modification;
•	Conduct training or refreshment the Collateral Methodology to ensure implementation is fully applying;
•	Keeping all collateral methodology are updated to sustain risk mitigation with competitive advantages, profitability and growth;
•	Other task assigned by hiring manager.

Job Requirement:
•	Bachelor of Business Administration in Banking and Finance or related field;
•	At least two years in collateral assessment and methodology development, or loan appraisal in MFI or banking sector;
•	Property valuation concept;
•	Banking product knowledge preferable; 
•	Strong in analytical skills;
•	Well mastered in communication skills in both Khmer and English;
•	Self-motivation and team player; 
•	Good computer literacy.

